Fix Advanpix Mahler early-exit threshold check (correctness).

`mps_mahler_check_stop` marks a polynomial as over-threshold when

    R > T || abs(R - r) > T

where R is the centre of an Aberth inclusion disk and r its radius.
Two problems with that predicate:

1. `abs` resolves to the integer abs(int) from <stdlib.h>, not fabs.
   With r ~ 1e-14 the expression abs(R-r) truncates to zero, making
   the second disjunct effectively dead.

2. `R > T` alone is optimistic. The true root can sit anywhere in
   [R - r, R + r]; to decide "definitely outside the threshold
   circle" we need

       R - r > T.

   With the old check the estimator can return 2*T (i.e. "reject") for
   a polynomial whose true Mahler measure is actually below T, and
   psmm.cpp will silently drop it. On long-running searches near
   M(p) = 1.3 this can prune valid candidates.

Replace all three phase-specific checks (float / DPE / MP) with the
provably-safe R - r > T.

Applies on top of 0001-advanpix-mahler-early-exit-api.patch.

Author: Pavel Holoborodko <pavel@advanpix.com>

